      • createAssignment

        public Assignment createAssignment​(java.lang.String assignmentName,
                                   java.lang.String shortDescription,
                                   java.lang.String institution,
                                   java.nio.file.Path instructionFile,
                                   java.util.Date dueDate,
                                   int[] sections,
                                   java.lang.String courseName,
                                   java.lang.String homeworkType,
                                   int maxGrade,
                                   int maxAttempts,
                                   java.util.List<Tests> testNames,
                                   java.lang.String unitTestName,
                                   java.lang.Long unitTestTimeLimit,
                                   java.nio.file.Path exampleImplementation,
                                   java.nio.file.Path testerClass,
                                   java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> forbiddenStatements)
                            throws java.io.IOException,
                                   BadExampleException
        Creates a new assignment and assigns it to students taking the specified course in the specified sections
        Parameters:
        assignmentName - The name or title of the assignment
        shortDescription - A short description of the assignment
        institution - The institution offering the course this assignment is a part of
        instructionFile - The instruction file
        dueDate - The due date for the assignment
        sections - The sections this assignment is for
        courseName - The name of the course this assignment is a part of
        homeworkType - The type of the assignment
        maxGrade - The maximum grade for this assignment
        maxAttempts - The maximum attempts allowed for this assignment
        testNames - A list of the tests applied to the submissions
        unitTestName - The name of the unit test, if it is applied
        unitTestTimeLimit - The time limit for the unit test in milliseconds. A value of 0 indicates no time limit
        testerClass - The tester class for the unit test, if there's any
        exampleImplementation - The example implementation from which the correct unit test output is generated
        forbiddenStatements - The statements to check for in the ForbiddenStatementChecker if applicable
        Returns:
        The newly created assignment instance
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If processing the instructions fails
        BadExampleException - If the example implementation or the tester do not compile or generate a runtime error (Determined by a non-zero exit code)
